cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning model for the interpretation and classification of mammograms and chest radiographic radiology reports. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The model also involves natural language processing (NLP) for the analysis of radiology reports, which could be classified under information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the study involves medical imaging (cs.MM) as it deals with the interpretation of mammograms and chest radiographs.
